<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_df65a08c-2c13-4a15-9b72-7c1cf5226562" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>12.4.5</sptc><title id="_d9ccc7f4-c9e1-420b-a81d-063687f515fb">Installation of free standing heating appliances</title><archive-num>2019: 3.10.7.5</archive-num><subclause id="_5f5fbfc0-f76e-44cc-9381-3a00be652015" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_9e377a92-6562-450e-b671-77fd4d9b062e">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The installation of a free standing heating appliance must comply with the following:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_15128170-6d38-40cf-a759-9d4f6a341265">The appliance must—<ol><li>be installed with safety clearances determined by testing in accordance with AS/NZS 2918; or</li><li>be located not less than 1.2 m from adjoining walls (other than a masonry wall); or</li><li>have a heat shield between the adjoining wall (other than a masonry wall) and the heating appliance in accordance with <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/907_0.8.0.xml#_58e69c30-c4bd-4676-8882-a547b105907a" id="_6e7c9c93-6ca6-4638-9d32-3fd64d221615" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5a</xref> and <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/908_0.8.0.xml#_ba9370ef-9d12-40b2-87bd-a49b6a4bcb4f" id="_8602ffb3-6d11-4018-b612-ed8cfc58766d" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5b</xref>.</li></ol></li><li id="_d772be89-6fb7-4608-bc3c-8cb2f38ce895">Where a heat shield is used, it must be installed in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/907_0.8.0.xml#_58e69c30-c4bd-4676-8882-a547b105907a" id="_1e988b06-e821-4770-bf81-2929e7543a79" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5a</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/908_0.8.0.xml#_ba9370ef-9d12-40b2-87bd-a49b6a4bcb4f" id="_be10fa41-e3a2-49e6-aff4-36fbe8eecd15" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5b</xref>, and—<ol><li id="_7440ef25-bf11-4256-9e5e-bd20daefaf86">have an FRL of not less than 60/60/60; or</li><li>be not less than 90 mm thick masonry constructed in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1807#_c1e7a2da-3ebf-4007-9f08-134efafe0279" id="_51e5d934-3fa6-4b13-9a98-a0b7a88fb6f5" publishing-id="vol2" scope="external" type="clause">H1D5</xref>.</li></ol></li><li id="_b989f296-3c25-4576-a087-8ad65a9b2304">The heating appliance must be installed on a hearth—<ol><li>complying with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/2661_1.7.0.xml#_ef86e29f-51cb-46c5-a25e-413f5188dfba" id="_868d2f88-84df-4c85-bf47-ddee14067032" scope="local" type="clause">12.4.2(b)</xref>, except that the hearth must extend 400 mm from the front and sides of the appliance in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/907_0.8.0.xml#_58e69c30-c4bd-4676-8882-a547b105907a" id="_f3ff66b5-8511-4ca8-b51e-0b1a9b0f8641" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5a</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/908_0.8.0.xml#_ba9370ef-9d12-40b2-87bd-a49b6a4bcb4f" id="_5c1c9462-3aca-4dd4-9b69-8bdb26065779" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5b</xref>; or</li><li>where a heat shield is installed, in accordance with <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/907_0.8.0.xml#_58e69c30-c4bd-4676-8882-a547b105907a" id="_3a56380b-9d24-4fe8-9d0b-f8c730c975f4" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5a</xref> and <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/908_0.8.0.xml#_ba9370ef-9d12-40b2-87bd-a49b6a4bcb4f" id="_554cc5f6-7a49-4339-a4be-b86e55e2633b" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5b</xref>.</li></ol></li><li id="_29ef2c01-5bd2-46ff-bcc2-69bef32ecdb7">The flue must—<ol><li>have been tested and passed the tests required by AS/NZS 2918; and</li><li>be installed in accordance with <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/909_0.12.0.xml#_5eb7daf4-d0bb-42db-85be-fc0297964767" id="_d2864ddc-1a42-47a1-8df2-5e3c2bda1350" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5c</xref>; and</li><li>terminate in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/906_0.7.0.xml#_2e89ef8e-308b-411f-b5a9-81503d82271c" id="_6fddb7c6-c974-4f4b-820a-652478f10972" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.3</xref>; and</li><li>be flashed in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1810#_0d2aa0e1-a433-4957-afe9-3f42634b7b2d" id="_d216d24b-23c7-46ca-90b8-1b764f886c39" publishing-id="vol2" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">H1D7</xref>.</li></ol></li><li id="_263d0729-c3c5-4c68-8652-3c74936a9d89">Flue types or installation of flues in areas not specifically covered by <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/907_0.8.0.xml#_58e69c30-c4bd-4676-8882-a547b105907a" id="_5d07d387-fade-4ecf-82a6-8d471a62bc7b" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5a</xref> and <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/908_0.8.0.xml#_ba9370ef-9d12-40b2-87bd-a49b6a4bcb4f" id="_3f899474-dae2-4fd0-af8f-20f28434de7e" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5b</xref> and <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/909_0.12.0.xml#_5eb7daf4-d0bb-42db-85be-fc0297964767" id="_24f1efff-43b3-45cd-8199-60494b00b41a" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.5c</xref> must be installed in accordance with AS/NZS 2918.</li></ol></subclause><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/907_0.8.0.xml" id="_58e69c30-c4bd-4676-8882-a547b105907a"><num xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" inv:access="external">12.4.5a</num><title xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" id="_a8e3788e-e640-4ecf-8fa5-4ffdffec5890" inv:access="external">Acceptable location of free standing heating appliances — Elevation</title><image xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" alt="Acceptable location of free standing heating appliances — Elevation" height="835" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:12-4-5a-acceptable-location-of-free-standing-heating-appliances-elevation.eps" inv:access="external" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/908_0.8.0.xml" id="_ba9370ef-9d12-40b2-87bd-a49b6a4bcb4f"><num xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" inv:access="external">12.4.5b</num><title xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" id="_b6d8a6c2-756f-4981-8bfe-138813440f57" inv:access="external">Acceptable location of free standing heating appliances — Plan view</title><image xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" alt="Acceptable location of free standing heating appliances — Plan view" height="941" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:12-4-5b-acceptable-location-of-free-standing-heating-appliances-plan-view.eps" inv:access="external" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/909_0.12.0.xml" id="_5eb7daf4-d0bb-42db-85be-fc0297964767"><num>12.4.5c</num><title id="_c369935f-ee5c-4226-bd4e-2dcfea411731">Acceptable flue installation details</title><image alt="Acceptable flue installation details" height="1414" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:12-4-5c-acceptable-flue-installation-details.eps" width="1200" widthdpi="200"><image height="1414" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_9642670c-596f-4768-81e6-4169af62260f.jpg" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image><desc-note id="_021b5842-4de0-43e1-be0b-3bc508042ec4"><p>Flue pipe size — 150 mm maximum (for other sizes see AS/NZS 2918).</p></desc-note></image-reference><callout id="_57bb135f-230e-4093-a5da-543cd807f961"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>References to AS/NZS 2918 in 12.4.5(a)(i) and (d)(i) are only applicable in the context in which they are referred to in accordance with A4G1(2). 12.4.5(a) provides three options for the installation of free standing heating appliances. Where 12.4.5(a)(i) is chosen as a solution the free standing heating appliance must be installed with safety clearances determined by testing in accordance with AS/NZS 2918. 12.4.5(d)(i), in addition to (d)(ii) and (d)(iii), require the flue to be tested and have passed the tests required by AS/NZS 2918.</p></callout></clause>